FBIS3-2304 "drchi045_w_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 HONG KONG & MACAO Hong Kong Hong Kong CPPCC Members Blame UK on Hong Kong Issue OW0803034794 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Mar 94 OW0803034794 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Mar 94 Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [From the "National News Hookup" program] [Text] Hong Kong members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC] who are to attend the Second Session of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee left Hong Kong for Beijing by plane at noon today. [Begin recording] [Unidentified CPPCC member] I think everyone has now clearly seen that during the remaining time, it is impossible to place our hopes on the British side for cooperation for a smooth transition of power. [Second unidentified CPPCC member] Now, the Hong Kong issue is not whether or not we want democracy. The process for democracy has been properly arranged by the Basic Law. It includes a method by which we can proceed in an orderly way and step by step. It can enable Hong Kong to develop properly and to prosper today, tomorrow, and in the future. The complications and the causes have all been created by the British side, which has ulterior motives. Therefore, the compatriots in Hong Kong and the people in China will not agree with them. [end recording]
